1
00:01:53,200 --> 00:01:54,997
I love you, Billy.

2
00:01:58,760 --> 00:02:00,990
I love you too, Mommy.

3
00:02:07,120 --> 00:02:08,394
Night-night.

4
00:02:11,504 --> 00:02:12,903
Sleep tight.

5
00:02:15,704 --> 00:02:18,093
Don't let the bedbugs bite.

6
00:02:19,784 --> 00:02:23,094
I'll see you in the morning light.

7
00:02:33,464 --> 00:02:35,102
I love you.

8
00:02:56,224 --> 00:02:59,341
They're going to make me an assistant
art director. So Kenny says:

9
00:02:59,544 --> 00:03:01,978
"You get yourself a Burberry coat.

10
00:03:02,224 --> 00:03:05,694
If you're gonna be Madison Avenue,
you have to look it."

11
00:03:05,904 --> 00:03:08,338
Saturday afternoon, I go out,
and it's cold.

12
00:03:08,584 --> 00:03:11,496
I go to this place
that specializes in Burberrys...

13
00:03:11,744 --> 00:03:14,338
...and say, " I want a Burberry coat,
37 short."

14
00:03:14,584 --> 00:03:17,337
They put it on,
and I look beautiful in it.

15
00:03:17,584 --> 00:03:18,733
I say, " I'll buy it."

16
00:03:18,944 --> 00:03:21,060
And right then, I start to sweat.

17
00:03:21,264 --> 00:03:25,177
I take my checkbook out, start to
sign the check, and my hand shakes...

18
00:03:25,424 --> 00:03:27,142
...because I'm so scared.

19
00:03:27,384 --> 00:03:28,783
- Good night.
- Where you going?

20
00:03:29,024 --> 00:03:32,699
- I gotta get home.
- Oh, Jesus, I gotta go.

21
00:03:32,904 --> 00:03:34,178
Okay, so let me finish.

22
00:03:34,424 --> 00:03:36,858
So I sign it,
and my hand starts shaking...

23
00:03:38,304 --> 00:03:41,740
Who is this? Danny, right?
Taxi!

24
00:03:41,984 --> 00:03:46,102
- Come on, I gotta tell you something.
- I can't. I gotta get home.

25
00:03:46,344 --> 00:03:48,938
Gotta talk to you
about something important.

26
00:03:49,184 --> 00:03:52,494
I'm putting you in charge
of the Mid-Atlantic account.

27
00:04:13,424 --> 00:04:16,416
By the end of the year, we'll
have them up to 10 million.

28
00:04:16,624 --> 00:04:19,741
If this campaign works out the way
I know it will...

29
00:04:19,984 --> 00:04:21,781
...they'll offer me a partnership.

30
00:04:21,984 --> 00:04:23,303
That's terrific!

31
00:04:23,504 --> 00:04:27,702
When that happens, I just want you
to know I'm taking you along.

32
00:04:28,984 --> 00:04:32,772
Wow! Wow! That's terrific.

33
00:04:49,584 --> 00:04:51,495
Joanna.

34
00:04:52,104 --> 00:04:53,742
I'm home.

35
00:04:56,704 --> 00:04:59,901
I forgot my keys. I gotta call
the office before they go.

36
00:05:00,144 --> 00:05:03,500
Jo, you're gonna be real proud
of me. I got good news.

37
00:05:05,904 --> 00:05:08,702
- Ted.
- One second. Let me just do this.

38
00:05:12,224 --> 00:05:15,341
You know Jack Edwards in accounting?
He committed suicide.

39
00:05:15,584 --> 00:05:17,575
Yeah, hi. Ted Kramer.

40
00:05:17,824 --> 00:05:21,499
I gotta get those photos from
the retoucher by tomorrow morning.

41
00:05:21,744 --> 00:05:24,338
- I'm leaving you.
- Honey, please. I can't hear.

42
00:05:25,944 --> 00:05:28,663
Okay, you too. Thanks a lot.
See you tomorrow.

43
00:05:29,264 --> 00:05:30,663
Did you guys eat?

44
00:05:30,904 --> 00:05:31,780
I'm leaving you.

45
00:05:34,744 --> 00:05:36,416
Here are my keys.

46
00:05:36,664 --> 00:05:39,656
Here's my American Express,
my Bloomingdale's card...

47
00:05:39,864 --> 00:05:43,573
...my checkbook. I've taken
$2000 out of our savings account.

48
00:05:43,784 --> 00:05:45,934
That's what I had when we got married.

49
00:05:46,184 --> 00:05:48,823
- Is this a joke?
- Here's the cleaning, laundry ticket.

50
00:05:49,064 --> 00:05:51,134
You can pick them both up
on Saturday.

51
00:05:51,344 --> 00:05:53,733
- You. You have to pick them up.
- What's wrong?

52
00:05:53,984 --> 00:05:57,613
I paid the rent, the Con Ed bill,
and the phone bill, so...

53
00:05:57,864 --> 00:05:59,536
You really pick your times to...

54
00:06:03,584 --> 00:06:07,293
I'm sorry I was late, but I was
busy making a living, all right?

55
00:06:08,064 --> 00:06:11,181
Come on, okay? Can we stop now?

56
00:06:11,424 --> 00:06:13,460
So that's everything.

57
00:06:18,464 --> 00:06:20,102
Enough, enough. All right?

58
00:06:20,344 --> 00:06:22,255
What are you doing?

59
00:06:22,544 --> 00:06:25,980
Where are you going? Just tell me
what I did that's so terrible.

60
00:06:26,224 --> 00:06:27,498
- It's not you.
- Then what?

61
00:06:27,744 --> 00:06:29,700
It's me. It's my fault.

62
00:06:30,144 --> 00:06:31,543
You married the wrong person.

63
00:06:31,784 --> 00:06:34,139
- I can't hack it.
- Let's just go inside.

64
00:06:34,384 --> 00:06:36,340
I can't, I tried.
I swear...

65
00:06:36,584 --> 00:06:39,337
Joanna, please, just... I'm sorry.

66
00:06:39,584 --> 00:06:44,499
- No, please don't make me go in there.
- I just want to talk.

67
00:06:44,744 --> 00:06:47,178
If you do, I swear, one day...

68
00:06:47,384 --> 00:06:49,818
...l'll go right out the window.
- Oh, please.

69
00:06:50,064 --> 00:06:52,259
Come on, now. What about Billy?

70
00:06:56,024 --> 00:06:59,300
I'm not taking him with me.
I'm no good for him.

71
00:06:59,784 --> 00:07:01,137
I'm terrible with him.

72
00:07:01,384 --> 00:07:04,103
I have no patience.

73
00:07:04,304 --> 00:07:06,295
He's better off without me.

74
00:07:08,384 --> 00:07:09,817
Joanna, please.

75
00:07:14,464 --> 00:07:16,694
And I don't love you anymore.

76
00:07:18,584 --> 00:07:20,495
- Where are you going?
- I don't know.

77
00:07:53,504 --> 00:07:56,701
Hi, Margaret. This is Ted.
Is my wife there?

78
00:07:56,904 --> 00:07:59,941
Yeah. Joanna come in?

79
00:08:00,184 --> 00:08:04,302
We had a little fight. I thought
she might have stopped by.

80
00:08:04,504 --> 00:08:07,701
If she comes in, tell her to come up
or just give me a ring.

81
00:08:09,504 --> 00:08:13,497
Don't worry. She didn't take
her suitcase. She won't get very far.

82
00:08:14,624 --> 00:08:17,821
I got work to do.
If she comes in, tell her to call me.

83
00:08:24,624 --> 00:08:26,103
It's about time.

84
00:08:29,024 --> 00:08:31,777
Joanna, that's the most insensitive...
Hi, Margaret.

85
00:08:32,024 --> 00:08:35,699
- She packed a suitcase?
- Look, it's nothing serious, really.

86
00:08:35,944 --> 00:08:37,821
She tell you where she was going?

87
00:08:38,064 --> 00:08:40,703
- You tell me.
- How would I know? I wasn't here.

88
00:08:40,944 --> 00:08:44,300
Clearly, you two had many
talks about my shortcomings...

89
00:08:44,504 --> 00:08:47,416
...which I haven't been privy to.
And I'd love to talk...

90
00:08:47,664 --> 00:08:50,781
...but I have a major presentation
in the morning...

91
00:08:51,024 --> 00:08:53,743
...and I gotta get my work done.
So please allow me...

92
00:08:53,984 --> 00:08:56,498
You don't realize
we have a serious problem.

93
00:08:56,704 --> 00:08:59,537
Wrong. Me. I got the problem.
All you gotta do is...

94
00:08:59,784 --> 00:09:02,059
...go out the door and go back to bed.

95
00:09:02,464 --> 00:09:04,898
- The fact is...
- For six months...

96
00:09:05,144 --> 00:09:08,580
...l've been spitting blood to get
this agency its biggest account.

97
00:09:08,824 --> 00:09:10,815
And at five, we got it.

98
00:09:11,584 --> 00:09:15,896
At eight, the vice president tells me
I'll be the next creative director.

99
00:09:16,104 --> 00:09:18,572
I come through this door
to share with my wife...

100
00:09:18,784 --> 00:09:22,333
...one of the five best days
of my life, and she looks at me...

101
00:09:22,584 --> 00:09:25,098
...and tells me she doesn't want
to live with me!

102
00:09:30,384 --> 00:09:32,898
Can't you understand
what she's done to me?

103
00:09:34,784 --> 00:09:38,094
She loused up one of the five
best days of your life.

104
00:09:41,864 --> 00:09:44,139
You're terrific. Boy, you're...

105
00:09:44,384 --> 00:09:46,295
Thanks very much, really.

106
00:09:47,904 --> 00:09:49,383
Sisterhood.

107
00:09:49,624 --> 00:09:51,740
Thank you for coming
to cheer me up, but...

108
00:09:52,064 --> 00:09:53,941
I didn't come to cheer you up.

109
00:09:54,184 --> 00:09:56,015
I'm concerned about Joanna.

110
00:09:56,544 --> 00:09:59,900
Maybe you can be concerned
in the privacy of your own apartment.

111
00:10:00,864 --> 00:10:05,016
Joanna and I never had any problems
until you and Charley split up.

112
00:10:05,264 --> 00:10:07,141
Oh, I don't believe you.

113
00:10:07,384 --> 00:10:09,102
Just tell me the truth, okay?

114
00:10:09,344 --> 00:10:10,936
Did you set her up to this?

115
00:10:11,184 --> 00:10:13,015
No, I didn't put her up to this.

116
00:10:13,264 --> 00:10:15,573
- Give her a little pep talk?
- No, I didn't.

117
00:10:15,824 --> 00:10:17,735
Joanna and I talk a great deal.

118
00:10:17,984 --> 00:10:20,020
And Joanna is a very unhappy woman.

119
00:10:20,264 --> 00:10:24,542
And it took a lot of courage for her
to walk out of here.

120
00:10:24,784 --> 00:10:27,696
How much courage does it take
to walk out on your kid?

121
00:11:38,944 --> 00:11:40,297
Where's Mommy?

122
00:11:40,544 --> 00:11:42,102
- What?
- Where's Mommy?

123
00:11:42,304 --> 00:11:43,703
What time is it?

124
00:11:44,904 --> 00:11:49,500
The little hand's on the 7, the big
hand's on the 9. Where's Mommy?

125
00:11:51,264 --> 00:11:56,133
Oh, God. Okay, I'm gonna tell you.
You want to know where Mommy is?

126
00:11:56,344 --> 00:11:59,541
- She's supposed to take me to school.
- She told me to do it.

127
00:11:59,744 --> 00:12:01,621
Okay, I'll tell you where she went.

128
00:12:01,824 --> 00:12:05,373
You know when you and your friends
don't get along and fight?

129
00:12:05,584 --> 00:12:08,098
And you want to go and be alone
for a while?

130
00:12:08,304 --> 00:12:10,864
Sometimes Mommy and Daddy
don't get along...

131
00:12:11,064 --> 00:12:14,693
...and one of them wants to go
and be by themselves for a while.

132
00:12:14,904 --> 00:12:17,134
- When is Mommy coming back?
- Soon.

133
00:12:17,384 --> 00:12:20,740
Now we are gonna have breakfast!
Okay? Just you and me.

134
00:12:20,984 --> 00:12:23,020
- What do you want?
- French toast.

135
00:12:23,384 --> 00:12:25,295
You want French toast, you got it.

136
00:12:25,504 --> 00:12:28,541
Put up a little water for Daddy
to have some coffee.

137
00:12:28,784 --> 00:12:31,696
We got how many eggs?
Two for you and two for me.

138
00:12:31,944 --> 00:12:32,933
We got milk.

139
00:12:33,184 --> 00:12:34,537
We got butter.

140
00:12:34,784 --> 00:12:36,502
We got $5.

141
00:12:36,704 --> 00:12:39,093
I got $5.
Here, you sit here.

142
00:12:39,864 --> 00:12:42,503
Okay, can you be my number one helper?

143
00:12:44,264 --> 00:12:45,413
Watch this. One hand.

144
00:12:46,184 --> 00:12:47,503
Here we go.

145
00:12:47,704 --> 00:12:50,423
Did you know that all
the best chefs are men?

146
00:12:50,664 --> 00:12:53,701
Isn't this terrific?
We gotta do this more often.

147
00:12:53,904 --> 00:12:56,293
- You dropped some shell in it.
- That's okay.

148
00:12:56,704 --> 00:12:59,980
Makes it crunchier.
You like it crunchy, don't you?

149
00:13:00,184 --> 00:13:03,893
Why don't you beat them,
and I'll get everything else going.

150
00:13:04,144 --> 00:13:06,021
- What time is school?
- 8:30.

151
00:13:06,264 --> 00:13:10,257
Gotta get the show on the road.
I gotta shower, shave and shampoo.

152
00:13:10,504 --> 00:13:11,539
I got people to see.

153
00:13:11,784 --> 00:13:14,218
And Daddy's gotta bring home
the bacon...

154
00:13:14,424 --> 00:13:15,857
...and he's gotta cook it.

155
00:13:16,264 --> 00:13:19,142
We're having a good time!
Where does Mommy keep the...?

156
00:13:19,544 --> 00:13:21,580
- In the stove.
- The pan. The stove.

157
00:13:23,784 --> 00:13:25,297
First, we need a nice fire.

158
00:13:26,144 --> 00:13:28,135
No, you're not doing it right.

159
00:13:28,384 --> 00:13:31,694
Look, you gotta do it fast. See?
It's the wrist.

160
00:13:31,904 --> 00:13:33,701
So the gucky part dissolves.

161
00:13:33,904 --> 00:13:37,533
Then you take the bread, and we...

162
00:13:37,784 --> 00:13:39,376
We...

163
00:13:40,304 --> 00:13:43,296
We fold the French toast.
That's what we do.

164
00:13:43,544 --> 00:13:46,934
- I think you forgot milk.
- I didn't. Milk comes last.

165
00:13:48,144 --> 00:13:50,704
When you're having a good time
you forget things.

166
00:13:51,384 --> 00:13:54,456
I just wanted to see
if you're paying attention.

167
00:13:54,984 --> 00:13:58,340
Fun, isn't it? When's the last
time Mommy let you in the kitchen?

168
00:13:58,584 --> 00:13:59,983
I don't like it in pieces.

169
00:14:00,224 --> 00:14:04,137
It tastes the same whether it's in
pieces or whole. Bread is bread.

170
00:14:04,424 --> 00:14:06,699
Besides, French toast
is always folded.

171
00:14:06,944 --> 00:14:10,016
In the best restaurants,
you see folded French toast.

172
00:14:10,304 --> 00:14:12,101
You get more bites that way.

173
00:14:13,864 --> 00:14:16,936
And while that's going,
Daddy's gonna make coffee.

174
00:14:17,184 --> 00:14:18,697
You having a good time?

175
00:14:18,904 --> 00:14:22,340
I don't remember the last
time I had such a good time.

176
00:14:23,264 --> 00:14:25,061
Daddy's gonna make himself coffee.

177
00:14:25,304 --> 00:14:27,613
- That's too much!
- No, I like it strong.

178
00:14:27,864 --> 00:14:29,900
Mommy always makes it too weak.

179
00:14:32,024 --> 00:14:33,901
Can I have some orange juice?

180
00:14:34,704 --> 00:14:36,934
Right. One OJ coming up
for the kid.

181
00:14:39,344 --> 00:14:40,743
Daddy, it's burning!

182
00:14:41,504 --> 00:14:43,096
- What?
- It's burning!

183
00:14:44,944 --> 00:14:47,822
Damn it! Goddamn her!

184
00:14:50,824 --> 00:14:52,496
Oh, shit.

185
00:14:54,624 --> 00:14:58,219
Just take it easy.
Everything is fine. We're terrific.

186
00:14:58,464 --> 00:14:59,897
Just...

187
00:15:01,224 --> 00:15:04,296
Just take it easy.
Nothing is the matter.

188
00:15:07,864 --> 00:15:09,217
- What?
- Your hand's sweaty.

189
00:15:09,464 --> 00:15:11,898
- When's Mommy coming back?
- Soon. I told you.

190
00:15:12,144 --> 00:15:15,341
- Is she gonna pick me up?
- Probably. If she doesn't, I will.

191
00:15:15,544 --> 00:15:17,341
- What if you forget?
- I won't.

192
00:15:17,584 --> 00:15:20,781
- What if you get run over?
- Mommy will pick you up.

193
00:15:21,024 --> 00:15:23,094
- Miss! What grade are you in?
- First.

194
00:15:23,304 --> 00:15:25,738
This is Billy Kramer.
He's in first grade.

195
00:15:25,944 --> 00:15:28,219
Take care of him. I gotta
get a taxi, I'm late. Taxi!

196
00:15:28,984 --> 00:15:30,337
Taxi!

197
00:15:33,024 --> 00:15:35,777
- Congratulations about Mid-Atlantic.
- Thanks.

198
00:15:36,024 --> 00:15:39,300
- Congratulations.
- Is the stuff back from the retoucher?

199
00:15:39,504 --> 00:15:41,734
- Great news, Ted.
- Thanks a lot.

200
00:15:41,984 --> 00:15:44,293
Morning. 11:00, meeting
with Airwick...

201
00:15:44,544 --> 00:15:47,695
- Where's the stuff from the retoucher?
- Right here.

202
00:15:48,344 --> 00:15:49,697
- Did my wife call?
- No.

203
00:15:49,944 --> 00:15:53,095
You're gonna have to cancel
the Airwick at 11:30.

204
00:16:23,024 --> 00:16:26,141
She's never gone this far before,
but in the past...

205
00:16:26,384 --> 00:16:29,103
...l've known
when she's upset because...

206
00:16:29,344 --> 00:16:30,936
...she gets very quiet.

207
00:16:31,184 --> 00:16:34,574
Our pattern has been that I've said,
"What's the matter?"...

208
00:16:34,784 --> 00:16:36,615
...and she'll kind of sit on it.

209
00:16:36,864 --> 00:16:39,776
But in the last few weeks,
maybe couple of months...

210
00:16:39,984 --> 00:16:43,772
...since we've been going crazy
with this account, I've been remiss.

211
00:16:44,024 --> 00:16:49,144
And I just didn't look at the writing
on the wall, so she's kind of...

212
00:16:49,664 --> 00:16:53,100
I think this is a way
of making me stop, look and say:

213
00:16:53,304 --> 00:16:55,340
" I'm as important as your work."

214
00:16:57,544 --> 00:16:59,535
Is there another guy?

215
00:17:01,464 --> 00:17:04,103
I don't think so.
She's not the type.

216
00:17:04,344 --> 00:17:07,097
She's got this friend, Margaret,
downstairs...

217
00:17:07,784 --> 00:17:11,902
...you know, women's lib.
I think they may have cooked this up.

218
00:17:12,904 --> 00:17:13,893
It worked.

219
00:17:15,184 --> 00:17:16,537
I'm going crazy!

220
00:17:16,784 --> 00:17:18,900
Look, not to worry.

221
00:17:19,104 --> 00:17:20,583
She'll be back.

222
00:17:20,824 --> 00:17:23,099
I didn't know it would happen to me!

223
00:17:24,064 --> 00:17:25,497
Don't let it get you down.

224
00:17:25,744 --> 00:17:29,054
I know she'll be back.
I'm terrific, really.

225
00:17:31,544 --> 00:17:34,263
- You do have a problem, Ted.
- Yeah, what's that?

226
00:17:37,064 --> 00:17:38,895
What are you gonna do about Billy?

227
00:17:40,584 --> 00:17:44,372
This just happened last night.
I'm sure when Joanna comes back...

228
00:17:44,584 --> 00:17:46,734
It's none of my business.
I'll butt out.

229
00:17:46,944 --> 00:17:49,458
Listen, I want to hear your thoughts.

230
00:17:49,704 --> 00:17:52,741
I appreciate you
taking the time to talk to me.

231
00:17:53,424 --> 00:17:57,337
May sound a little rough, but...

232
00:17:57,584 --> 00:18:01,702
...I think you ought to send Billy away
to stay with relatives for a while.

233
00:18:02,144 --> 00:18:04,499
You mean, until Joanna comes back?

234
00:18:05,304 --> 00:18:07,499
Suppose Joanna doesn't come back?

235
00:18:10,664 --> 00:18:12,302
Gee, I don't know...

236
00:18:12,544 --> 00:18:14,023
Ted, listen to me.

